---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="I'm an engineer and dad who got frustrated with vague baby gear reviews. So I started testing everything myself. Here's why I built GearForLittle."
>

  <!-- Page header -->
  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border-b border-neutral-200">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
      <nav class="text-xs text-neutral-400 mb-4" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-neutral-600 no-underline">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span>About</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">About GearForLittle</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        An engineer dad, a lot of spreadsheets, and a genuine hatred of vague product reviews.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 space-y-16">

    <!-- Intro with photo -->
    <section class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-10 items-start">
      <!-- Photo placeholder -->
      <div class="flex-shrink-0">
        <div class="w-36 h-36 rounded-2xl bg-neutral-200 flex items-center justify-center text-neutral-400 font-medium text-sm">
          Photo
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Text -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Hey, I'm [Your Name]</h2>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I'm a software engineer and a dad to [child's name], born in [year]. When my partner and I started building our registry, I did what engineers do: I opened a spreadsheet and started researching.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          Six weeks later, I had 40 tabs open, three conflicting "best of" lists, and zero confidence in any of them. Every review site I found was either recycling manufacturer specs or clearly optimizing for affiliate clicks over honesty.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why I Started This Site -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-5">Why I Started This Site</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none">
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The baby gear industry is a mess. Products are marketed with vague claims ("ultra-lightweight!" "easy to fold!"), prices are all over the place, and most review sites are ranking products by affiliate commission, not actual quality.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I bought the gear anyway, figured it out the hard way, and kept notes on all of it. After a year of parenting and testing, I had enough real-world data to actually be useful. So I built this site.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          GearForLittle is what I wish had existed when I was frantically Googling at 11pm. It's not trying to be everything to everyone. It's just one dad's thorough, honest take on the gear that actually matters.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How I'm Different -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6">How I'm Different</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        {[
          {
            icon: 'ðŸ“Š',
            title: 'I think in systems',
            body: 'Every review comes with a structured breakdown. Safety, ease of use, value, durability, and dad-friendliness â€” each scored separately so you can see exactly what you\'re trading off.',
          },
          {
            icon: 'ðŸ›’',
            title: 'I actually buy the products',
            body: 'No PR samples. No gifted gear. I spend my own money (or borrow from other parents) so that my incentives are aligned with yours.',
          },
          {
            icon: 'â±ï¸',
            title: 'Long-term testing',
            body: 'I use products for weeks or months before writing anything. That stroller you\'re eyeing? I\'ve folded it 200 times. That car seat? I\'ve installed it in three different cars.',
          },
          {
            icon: 'ðŸŽ¯',
            title: 'Dad perspective',
            body: 'Most baby gear is marketed to moms. I write for dads too â€” about carrier fit for broad shoulders, one-hand stroller folds, and whether something is genuinely intuitive or just "read the manual" intuitive.',
          },
        ].map(({ icon, title, body }) => (
          <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-neutral-200">
            <div class="text-2xl mb-3">{icon}</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">{title}</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">{body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- E-E-A-T: Credentials -->
    <section class="bg-secondary-900 text-white rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-5 text-white">Credentials &amp; Experience</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3">
        {[
          'Software engineer with [X] years of experience in product development',
          'Parent to [child\'s age] child â€” actively using and testing baby gear every day',
          'Reviewed [X+] baby products across [X] categories since [year]',
          'No brand partnerships, sponsorships, or free products accepted',
          'Active member of parenting communities and product research forums',
          'Read hundreds of JPMA and NHTSA safety reports for car seat coverage',
        ].map((item) => (
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-neutral-300">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-primary-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
            </svg>
            {item}
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact / CTA -->
    <section class="text-center border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Got a Question or Product Suggestion?</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-5">
        I read every email. If there's a product you want me to test, or something you think I got wrong, reach out.
      </p>
      <a
        href="mailto:hello@gearforlittle.com"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-primary-600 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-full hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors no-underline text-sm"
      >
        hello@gearforlittle.com
      </a>
      <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-neutral-100">
        <p class="text-xs text-neutral-400">
          See exactly how every product is evaluated on the{' '}
          <a href="/how-we-test" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline">How We Test</a> page.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
